`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- Rapier `castRay` with `solid=true` and ray origin just outside the capsule (below the bottom) is the simplest ground detection: no self-hits, no filter needed. The distance from `body.translation().y` to the capsule bottom equals `totalHeight/2`.
- Separating `isGrounded` as a pure-ish function (takes body/world/rapier as params) lets it be tested without a React context. The hook (`useJump`) just wires up the keydown listener and `useFrame` tick.
- Circular dependency is avoided by reading capsule dimensions from `grid.json` in both `useJump.ts` and `PlayerCapsule.tsx` — single source of truth without importing across component/hook boundaries.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`
